WEBVTT

00:04.004 --> 00:06.745
<i>♪</i>

00:09.009 --> 00:10.793
- Jeb, get down low.

00:10.836 --> 00:12.099
We're gonna hide, okay?

00:12.142 --> 00:13.535
So, come on.

00:13.578 --> 00:17.060
<i>♪</i>

00:18.844 --> 00:24.459
<i>♪</i>

00:24.502 --> 00:25.808
- Zurie.

00:25.851 --> 00:27.070
- Don't say anything.

00:27.114 --> 00:28.202
- Jeb.

00:31.683 --> 00:33.294
Are you hiding from me?

00:33.337 --> 00:35.383
I'll tell you one thing,

00:35.426 --> 00:39.474
we have seen a lot of ghosts
in this house lately.

00:39.517 --> 00:42.651
A lot of ghosts
and they--they like--

00:42.694 --> 00:46.133
- Jeb, be quiet.
- They love to get after kids

00:46.176 --> 00:49.223
who are hiding
from their Pappy.

00:52.269 --> 00:55.011
Oh, Mr. Ghost.

00:58.058 --> 00:59.624
'Cause I'm out of here.

01:03.106 --> 01:05.108
-
Got ya.

01:07.850 --> 01:10.157
- Jeb, take his shoes off
and tickle his feet.

01:13.073 --> 01:17.120
Hey.

01:17.164 --> 01:19.427
Go get my oxygen mask.

01:19.470 --> 01:21.516
- We don't want to kill him.
- No.

01:23.692 --> 01:24.867
<i>Tammy!</i>

01:24.910 --> 01:31.830
<i>♪</i>

01:49.413 --> 01:51.546
- Maybe we could do your
birthday and my birthday

01:51.589 --> 01:54.026
together and go down to
Austin that following weekend?

01:54.070 --> 01:55.202
- We can do that.
That'd be fun.

01:55.245 --> 01:57.117
Your birthday's
the 28th, right?

01:57.160 --> 02:00.207
- No, it's the 27th.
- 27th, my bad.

02:02.774 --> 02:05.212
- Chuck, sit.

02:06.474 --> 02:07.910
Sit.

02:07.953 --> 02:09.520
Hmm, whatever.

02:09.564 --> 02:12.088
On our ranch, we have horses,

02:12.132 --> 02:13.742
cows,

02:13.785 --> 02:18.181
dogs, but I can honestly say
that Chuck rules all.

02:18.225 --> 02:19.661
- He's the king around here.

02:24.144 --> 02:25.536
- Hi.
- Hi.

02:25.580 --> 02:27.147
- I'm Erin.
- Erin,

02:27.190 --> 02:28.670
nice to meet you.
- Yes, come on in.

02:28.713 --> 02:30.367
- Hey, there. How are you?
- This is my husband, Scott.

02:30.411 --> 02:31.890
- Scott, very nice to meet you.
- Hi, Scott. Nice to meet you.

02:31.934 --> 02:32.978
Who's this cutie pie?

02:33.022 --> 02:34.241
This is Chuck.

02:34.284 --> 02:36.591
- Hi, Chuck. Hello, my love.

02:36.634 --> 02:37.548
- Come on in.

02:37.592 --> 02:38.593
And with us having a baby...

02:38.636 --> 02:41.204
- Get out of here.

02:42.727 --> 02:44.729
- And Chuck being
our pride and joy,

02:44.773 --> 02:47.428
we thought that it'd be
good to bring someone

02:47.471 --> 02:49.430
in just to, kind of,
shed a little light

02:49.473 --> 02:51.040
on how Chuck feels about it.

02:52.694 --> 02:54.435
- I like to do
a little invocation

02:54.478 --> 02:57.438
to get us all
grounded and centered.

02:57.481 --> 03:00.484
We call now for our friends,
the archangels,

03:00.528 --> 03:03.705
and all of our ancestors
of the light and love.

03:03.748 --> 03:07.230
We ask that our power animals
known and unknown

03:07.274 --> 03:09.972
would join us
and we give thanks

03:10.015 --> 03:13.018
in advance for this wonderful
time we get to be together.

03:14.498 --> 03:16.848
What questions
do you have for him?

03:16.892 --> 03:18.067
- We're gonna have a baby.

03:18.110 --> 03:19.199
So what would--
- Wonderful.

03:19.242 --> 03:21.810
- How would Chuck feel
about a baby?

03:21.853 --> 03:23.464
What would he think of that?
- Good question.

03:23.507 --> 03:25.292
How would you feel, my love,

03:25.335 --> 03:28.469
if mom and dad
had a human baby?

03:35.693 --> 03:37.913
He said, "Okay, let's just
get this straight,

03:37.956 --> 03:42.352
"okay, as long as
baby's second and I'm first."

03:42.396 --> 03:44.006
-
- That's true.

03:44.049 --> 03:45.007
- Would that be all right?

03:51.970 --> 03:55.757
What I'm hearing is that,
"I would be the best

03:55.800 --> 03:58.281
"caretaker for the baby."
- Yup.

03:58.325 --> 04:02.198
- And, um, he's gonna be
a fine nanny for you.

04:02.242 --> 04:03.808
- Oh, I like that.

04:03.852 --> 04:05.984
<i>I feel a lot better knowing
now that Chuck</i>

04:06.028 --> 04:08.248
<i>is gonna be happy with
a little brother or sister,</i>

04:08.291 --> 04:10.032
but I don't think
Chuck's gonna babysit.

04:10.075 --> 04:11.207
Dad'll babysit.

04:11.251 --> 04:12.904
- You trust your dad
with a baby?

04:12.948 --> 04:13.905
- Not really.

04:15.298 --> 04:17.344
What does Chuck think of us?
- Oh, good question.

04:17.387 --> 04:18.823
- That's a good one.

04:18.867 --> 04:21.391
- So, sweetheart, what do you
think about mom and dad?

04:28.006 --> 04:30.313
Oh, he said,
"I'm being really nice to you

04:30.357 --> 04:32.141
"because you have treats."

04:32.184 --> 04:33.882
Is that it?

04:37.102 --> 04:43.935
<i>♪</i>

04:43.979 --> 04:45.328
- Hi.
- Hey.

04:45.372 --> 04:46.721
- What are you guys doing?
- What's going on, girl?

04:46.764 --> 04:48.723
- Just smoking cigars and--
- Where y'all been?

04:48.766 --> 04:52.379
- On the phone working
with the 525 Foundation.

04:52.422 --> 04:56.252
-
- Sorry.

04:56.296 --> 04:57.645
- It's fine.

04:57.688 --> 04:58.689
- But you weren't here
when we fired these up.

04:58.733 --> 05:00.082
- Yup.
- What y'all doing?

05:00.125 --> 05:03.477
- So because we work close
with the 525 Foundation,

05:03.520 --> 05:05.522
Lacey, you're going
to speak Thursday night

05:05.566 --> 05:07.611
about opioid addiction.

05:07.655 --> 05:11.746
- The 525 Foundation is set up
to inform the public,

05:11.789 --> 05:16.664
people, parents about the use
of opioids, pain killers.

05:16.707 --> 05:18.796
- It's the misuse
of the opioids

05:18.840 --> 05:21.364
that we need
to educate people about.

05:21.408 --> 05:24.541
<i>- And Lacey's been asked to
speak at the 525 gala</i>

05:24.585 --> 05:28.153
because this is cause
close to all of us.

05:28.197 --> 05:30.460
- Yeah.
- You don't realize

05:30.504 --> 05:31.896
the dangers out there.

05:31.940 --> 05:34.421
You just see the fun side,
I guess.

05:34.464 --> 05:35.944
- Right.
- And I'm have a pill

05:35.987 --> 05:38.773
and a little shot,
life's gonna be good.

05:38.816 --> 05:40.035
- Right.
- Well, look, that's--

05:40.078 --> 05:42.559
the exact words

05:42.603 --> 05:45.301
out of the coroner's mouth
the night Cody died

05:45.345 --> 05:48.739
was the combination of the
alcohol that they had drunk,

05:48.783 --> 05:51.655
along with the drug
they had taken,

05:51.699 --> 05:53.875
simply went to sleep
and didn't wake up

05:53.918 --> 05:56.747
because of the huge
sedative effect.

05:56.791 --> 05:59.881
<i>My son, Cody,
accidentally overdosed</i>

05:59.924 --> 06:03.406
and for the first
five, six, seven years

06:03.450 --> 06:06.061
I--I couldn't talk about it
because it's--

06:06.104 --> 06:07.497
people are so judgmental.

06:07.541 --> 06:09.630
You say that you
have a child that overdosed,

06:09.673 --> 06:12.154
people will still judge you
as a parent.

06:12.197 --> 06:14.635
- Bad parent.
- And they judge that child.

06:14.678 --> 06:17.159
It took me years to
be able to talk about it

06:17.202 --> 06:19.683
without getting over emotional.

06:19.727 --> 06:22.512
- You know, I didn't get to
know Cody that well.

06:22.556 --> 06:24.775
I wish I had got to--
- Yeah.

06:24.819 --> 06:26.690
- Know him as a young man.
- So do I.

06:26.734 --> 06:28.562
That, you know what,
that's the hard part

06:28.605 --> 06:29.737
is missing out on
what I didn't get to know.

06:29.780 --> 06:32.479
- How old would
he have been now, 30?

06:32.522 --> 06:34.437
30 what?
- Four years older than her.

06:34.481 --> 06:36.439
- Yeah, so 34.

06:36.483 --> 06:41.966
<i>♪</i>

06:42.010 --> 06:44.882
- So, Cody was
my older brother.

06:44.926 --> 06:46.493
In, like, every sense
of the word.

06:46.536 --> 06:48.886
You know, he just

06:48.930 --> 06:52.063
<i>had this personality that
everyone wanted to be around,</i>

06:52.107 --> 06:53.413
<i>including me.</i>

06:53.456 --> 06:55.240
They always take the best ones,
you know.

06:55.284 --> 06:56.764
<i>♪</i>

06:56.807 --> 06:59.767
I just want to use what
happened to him to help others,

06:59.810 --> 07:03.510
like, it can't be for nothing.

07:03.553 --> 07:07.992
Um, so if I can just stop
one family from

07:08.036 --> 07:11.387
having to go through this,
it'll be worth it.

07:11.431 --> 07:12.997
I definitely have an ugly cry.

07:13.041 --> 07:14.129
That's why
I had to turn around.

07:14.172 --> 07:16.044
I didn't want
to embarrass anybody.

07:16.087 --> 07:18.481
- You can give her
some tips on public speaking.

07:18.525 --> 07:19.961
- Cool.

07:20.004 --> 07:22.746
- Remember the time I got
pulled off the stage in Vegas?

07:22.790 --> 07:27.403
At one event, I was just
bantering back and forth

07:27.447 --> 07:31.233
and having fun with them before
I got into the presentation.

07:31.276 --> 07:34.497
He said I was wandering.

07:34.541 --> 07:36.499
He was all over the place.

07:36.543 --> 07:37.892
Got the hook.

07:37.935 --> 07:39.197
- You have a tendency
to do that.

07:39.241 --> 07:40.198
-
No, I don't.

07:40.242 --> 07:41.504
- You do.

07:41.548 --> 07:42.549
- No, I don't wander.
- You don't wander?

07:42.592 --> 07:44.986
- No.
- You don't?

07:45.029 --> 07:46.291
- No.

07:46.335 --> 07:47.554
- What did we start
talking about it, this?

07:47.597 --> 07:49.556
- When?
- Just now.

07:49.599 --> 07:51.035
- Who we talking about?

07:55.475 --> 07:58.521
Maybe I wandered a little more
than I normally wander.

08:05.223 --> 08:07.095
<i>♪</i>

08:09.706 --> 08:12.230
- Hey, everybody.

08:12.274 --> 08:13.667
How's that creamy ice?

08:13.710 --> 08:15.364
How about giving me a bite,
huh, boy?

08:15.407 --> 08:17.714
Name's Bubba W.

08:17.758 --> 08:19.063
How are y'all doing?

08:19.107 --> 08:22.458
- Good.
- It is good to see you.

08:22.502 --> 08:24.112
You, right there.
You, my friend.

08:24.155 --> 08:25.635
Hey, look who it is.

08:25.679 --> 08:27.811
- Hi, Pappy.
- Hey.

08:27.855 --> 08:29.291
Give Bubba W a hug.

08:29.334 --> 08:31.989
Oh, how you, little buddy?
Thank you very much.

08:32.033 --> 08:33.991
You give Bubba W a little hug?

08:34.035 --> 08:35.819
<i>♪</i>

08:35.863 --> 08:37.778
- Bubba W isn't even real.

08:37.821 --> 08:40.345
- Whoo, Bubba W doesn't know
what to think of that.

08:41.651 --> 08:48.789
<i>♪</i>

08:52.401 --> 08:53.271
- What are you doing?

08:54.229 --> 08:55.491
Ew.

08:55.535 --> 08:57.058
That's weird.

08:57.711 --> 08:58.973
Hank hates being clean.
- He's a pig.

08:59.016 --> 09:00.409
- He hates it.
- He's a pig.

09:03.586 --> 09:04.848
- Hello.
Where did you come from?

09:04.892 --> 09:07.024
- The herd is here.
- The herd.

09:07.068 --> 09:08.983
<i>♪</i>

09:09.026 --> 09:11.376
- Hey, can I pick your brain
for a bit?

09:11.420 --> 09:14.031
I've just been thinking
about the speech and I think--

09:14.075 --> 09:15.337
- Are you nervous?
- I'm a little nervous.

09:15.380 --> 09:17.339
I could use some advice.
- Okay, but that's okay.

09:17.382 --> 09:19.210
- Well, I've seen you speak
and, it's like,

09:19.254 --> 09:20.603
I'm not sure I have
the charisma that you have.

09:20.647 --> 09:21.778
- Yeah, you do.

09:23.171 --> 09:24.651
We're proud to be a part
of the ribbon cutting today

09:24.694 --> 09:25.826
and tomorrow night's
our banquet.

09:25.869 --> 09:28.045
My girls will be
looking pretty hot, Rob.

09:28.089 --> 09:29.264
You got a lot of money.

09:29.307 --> 09:31.005
I'll put you
in the right direction.

09:32.049 --> 09:33.224
- How did you go
from being, like,

09:33.268 --> 09:35.575
the star quarterback
to a public speaker?

09:35.618 --> 09:37.272
- In high school,
believe it or not,

09:37.315 --> 09:39.753
<i>your dad was a shy guy,</i>

09:39.796 --> 09:41.755
but when I got into speech,
I loved it.

09:41.798 --> 09:43.278
- Oh, really?
- It was just, like,

09:43.321 --> 09:45.410
the greatest,
I don't know what it was,

09:45.454 --> 09:49.545
but it was, like, I have
control of this entire room.

09:49.589 --> 09:53.331
You're telling stories and you
want to make them descriptive

09:53.375 --> 09:56.726
so they can see it
and make eye contact.

09:56.770 --> 09:58.946
Audiences get nervous
if you look nervous.

09:58.989 --> 10:01.122
It's like a horse, they get
nervous if you look nervous.

10:01.165 --> 10:02.906
- Okay.
- They start worrying.

10:02.950 --> 10:04.081
- What happens if
I get emotional?

10:04.125 --> 10:05.300
Like, what should
I--what are your--

10:05.343 --> 10:06.388
- That's okay.
- Right.

10:06.431 --> 10:08.390
- I have, literally,

10:08.433 --> 10:11.523
broken down giving a speech.

10:11.567 --> 10:13.743
- What was it about?
- It was about my grandfather.

10:13.787 --> 10:16.224
- Okay.
- And I bowed my head

10:16.267 --> 10:18.618
and bit my lip.

10:18.661 --> 10:19.749
- Yeah.
- 'Cause I said,

10:19.793 --> 10:20.750
"Hey--"
- Get it together, kind of.

10:20.794 --> 10:22.230
- Exactly.
- Yeah.

10:22.273 --> 10:27.409
- Be you. Gorgeous, personable,
sweet, loving, kind,

10:27.452 --> 10:28.410
big hearted you.
- That's me?

10:28.453 --> 10:29.454
- That's you.
- Awe.

10:29.498 --> 10:31.282
- And they will eat you up.

10:31.326 --> 10:33.197
- And then I got
big, tall heels on.

10:33.241 --> 10:35.635
I'll prob--my luck, I'll walk
across the stage and fall down

10:35.678 --> 10:36.853
or something.
- Hey, I've done it.

10:36.897 --> 10:38.594
I fell off the stage once.
- In your heels?

10:38.638 --> 10:39.682
- Not my heels, no.
- Oh.

10:39.726 --> 10:40.770
- No, I took them off.
-

10:40.814 --> 10:42.642
- Dang gum these heels.

10:45.296 --> 10:52.216
<i>♪</i>

10:53.609 --> 10:54.828
What's the word?

10:54.871 --> 10:57.134
- It's--that's not good.
- Hmm.

10:57.178 --> 10:59.920
This will be my last year
to breed on her.

10:59.963 --> 11:04.141
After this, she just
goes outside and she's a pet.

11:04.185 --> 11:07.971
We run an extensive
horse breeding operation,

11:08.015 --> 11:10.321
but this year
we were having trouble

11:10.365 --> 11:14.325
getting a majority of these
horses in full pregnant.

11:14.369 --> 11:16.545
Then Erin said,
"Dad, I got the solution."

11:16.588 --> 11:18.460
- Hi.
- Hi.

11:18.503 --> 11:20.984
I'm Sandra.
- Thank you so much for coming.

11:21.028 --> 11:23.726
Everybody,
this is a communicator.

11:23.770 --> 11:25.162
- Pet communicator.

11:31.038 --> 11:33.388
- You know, Sandra really
helped a lot with Chuck.

11:33.431 --> 11:34.955
- What I'm hearing is that

11:34.998 --> 11:39.046
"I would be the best caretaker
for the baby."

11:39.089 --> 11:40.612
- So, I feel like
she's gonna be able

11:40.656 --> 11:41.962
to help you a lot
with your horses.

11:42.005 --> 11:43.180
- I'll give it a shot.

11:43.224 --> 11:44.878
I've got a lot of mares
that just don't

11:44.921 --> 11:47.750
want to cooperate
with the studs.

11:47.794 --> 11:49.056
- So, not that
I'm already pregnant,

11:49.099 --> 11:50.753
you can bug this mare
to get pregnant instead.

11:53.582 --> 11:54.975
- Hey.
- Hello, my love.

11:55.018 --> 11:56.498
- Okay.
- Hello.

11:56.541 --> 11:58.892
- Okay, there. Talk to her.
- And what is her name?

11:58.935 --> 12:00.502
- You tell me.
- Oh, I don't know.

12:02.722 --> 12:06.421
My name is Sandra and I would
love to talk with you.

12:07.814 --> 12:09.206
Do you have a question for her?

12:09.250 --> 12:12.557
- Ask her, when she is going
to ovulate again

12:12.601 --> 12:14.777
'cause we need to know.
- You need to know.

12:14.821 --> 12:16.300
- I need you to ask her that.

12:16.344 --> 12:19.390
- Love, can you tell me
when you'll be ready for one?

12:25.527 --> 12:28.486
Well, the answer I hear is
about two months.

12:29.618 --> 12:30.575
I don't know
how that works but...

12:30.619 --> 12:31.881
- That don't work.

12:31.925 --> 12:34.101
We need her to get pregnant
in three weeks.

12:34.144 --> 12:36.059
- Oh, in three weeks? Okay.

12:36.103 --> 12:39.410
- But if she told you two
months, that tells me she's--

12:39.454 --> 12:41.282
she's just--
- She not ready yet.

12:41.325 --> 12:42.326
- She's not ready.

12:42.370 --> 12:44.415
You know, this is
a crazy question.

12:44.459 --> 12:46.896
Ask her who she would like
to be bred to.

12:46.940 --> 12:49.507
If she tells you that,
you've got a job.

12:49.551 --> 12:52.075
- Yeah.

12:52.119 --> 12:53.163
- I'm putting you
on the spot here.

12:53.207 --> 12:54.295
- You are putting me
on the spot.

12:54.338 --> 12:55.470
- But that's okay.

12:55.513 --> 12:56.819
- So, I'll see if
she has a preference.

13:01.519 --> 13:03.913
Well, what I'm hearing

13:03.957 --> 13:06.133
is he's a tall one

13:06.176 --> 13:07.917
with a gentle spirit.

13:07.961 --> 13:09.789
Do you have one like that?

13:09.832 --> 13:10.920
- No.

13:10.964 --> 13:12.095
You got to have--
- Ours are maneaters.

13:12.139 --> 13:13.923
Maneaters.
- Are they maneaters?

13:13.967 --> 13:16.099
- Yeah, I could be
a pet communicator.

13:16.143 --> 13:17.884
- You're a good
pet communicator.

13:17.927 --> 13:19.624
- You bet I am.

13:19.668 --> 13:20.974
Here, come here, sweetie.

13:22.497 --> 13:25.152
Dolly, are you
having a good day?

13:27.850 --> 13:30.113
Oh, do you like it
here at the ranch?

13:30.157 --> 13:31.245
Mm-hmm.

13:31.288 --> 13:33.203
Oh, look, do you like Annie?

13:36.032 --> 13:38.948
- He's losing it.
-

13:38.992 --> 13:40.994
Is this a happy barn?
- Yeah.

13:41.037 --> 13:44.475
I'm hearing, just joy coming
from everybody.

13:44.519 --> 13:46.173
These animals know
they're loved.

13:46.216 --> 13:47.652
- Thank you for coming.
- Oh, thank you

13:47.696 --> 13:48.828
for inviting me.
- Come on, I'll walk you out.

13:48.871 --> 13:50.133
- All right, sounds good.

13:50.177 --> 13:51.352
- You're holding up
the breeding program.

13:51.395 --> 13:52.832
- Oh, my goodness,
don't want to do that.

13:57.924 --> 14:01.710
<i>♪</i>

14:01.753 --> 14:05.366
<i>- Lucy, got someone here
who understands you.</i>

14:05.409 --> 14:08.021
- She tells me,
she's got the best life here.

14:08.064 --> 14:09.587
- Are you kidding me?

14:09.631 --> 14:12.547
